ari'a lie at the core of all Islamist revivalist ideologies and movements of the past two centuries. The demand for the implementation of Shari'a is one of the hallmarks of Islamic fundamentalism, and Shari'a has become one of the most controversial and politicized concepts in Muslim-majority countries today. This is one of the first books to examine how Muslims understand and apply Shari'a in contemporary societies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 4aLaw -- International and Comparative Law. 4aMiddle East Studies. 4aPolitics -- Middle East. 7aRELIGION / Islam / Law.2bisacsh1 aAkhavi, Shahrough, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAmanat, Abbas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAmanat, Abbas, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aArjomand, Saïd Amir, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFeldman, Noah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGriffel, Frank, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGriffel, Frank, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJohnston, David L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrämer, Gudrun, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMottahedeh, Roy P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOpwis, Felicitas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWürth, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080477953140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804779531423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780804779531/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles